TEXT.P:
Central Bank of China (CBC) officials said Taiwan contractors and
suppliers are welcome to bid for contracts in nine major categories
of ADB-initiated development projects in developing Asian countries,
including electricity; reservoir, dam and water supply;
transportation; telecommunications; education; medicine; agriculture;
and fisheries.

-- Locally produced natural gas for domestic use that is sold to
re-sellers will fall in price from NT$7.75 to NT$6.89 per cubic
meter;

-- Imported natural gas for domestic use that is sold to
re-sellers will fall in price from NT$8.62 to NT$7.66 per cubic
meter;

-- All Cabinet-level departments should reach a consensus before
any government policy is made public, and use the power of the media
to support the implementation of the policy;

-- The Central Bank of China (CBC) should raise interest rates
for all other banks' deposit reserves in the CBC in order to increase
banks' self-owned capital;

-- The government should issue government bonds and treasury
bills to purchase blue chip stocks when their market prices fall
to less than their net values;

DOC.TEXT:
The lead stories in major Taiwan dailies
Saturday are as follows:

@The Central Daily News: President Lee said the government will
take measures to rebuild investors' confidence and to stabilize
capital market.

@The China Times: Business tax for bank institutions will be
lowered to 2 percent.

@The United Daily News: The government announced measures to
rejuvenate the sagging stock market.

@The Liberty Times: The Finance Ministry announces a five-point
measure to stabilize capital market.

@The Commons Daily: The Finance Ministry adopts measures to
strengthen financial systems.

@The China Post: MOF announced initiatives to firm up the stock
market.

@The China News: Banks' reserve ratio will be slashed.

